Sentencas: In fuel cell applications, the cells must be able to withstand varying operating conditions.
Titulo: Durability Study of SOFCs Under Cycling Current Load Conditions

Sentencas: Anode supported solid oxide fuel cells were tested under cycling current load in order to determine the durability and possibly identify degradation mechanisms.
Titulo: Durability Study of SOFCs Under Cycling Current Load Conditions

Sentencas: At 750 degrees C and a cycling between zero and 0.75 A cm(-2), the cell voltage degradation rate was similar to tests with the corresponding high constant current density.
Titulo: Durability Study of SOFCs Under Cycling Current Load Conditions

Sentencas: However, by analyzing the impedance spectra it was found that anode degradation was becoming more important when going from constant to cycling conditions.
Titulo: Durability Study of SOFCs Under Cycling Current Load Conditions

Sentencas: Running the cycling load tests at 850 degrees C, the cells degraded similarly as under the corresponding constant current load whereas, in some cases, cells failed mechanically after a few hundred hours.
Titulo: Durability Study of SOFCs Under Cycling Current Load Conditions

Sentencas: These cells did not experience severe additional degradation due to the cycling of the current density until the point of failure.
Titulo: Durability Study of SOFCs Under Cycling Current Load Conditions

Sentencas: The mechanical failure could be avoided if the cells were sealed to an interconnect rather than directly to an alumina test house.
Titulo: Durability Study of SOFCs Under Cycling Current Load Conditions

Sentencas: The degradation is discussed in the light of testing setup and conditions and cycling parameters.
Titulo: Durability Study of SOFCs Under Cycling Current Load Conditions
